UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1353
1 AN ACT relating to professional engineering and land surveying scholarships.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 322 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 It is the intent of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky to:
6 (1) Ensure the availability of professional engineers and professional land surveyors
7 in the Commonwealth; and
8 (2) Address professional engineer and professional land surveyor workforce
9 development and needs throughout the Commonwealth by providing eligible
10 Kentucky residents with scholarships to:
11 (a) Attend a qualifying program at a postsecondary institution in the
12 Commonwealth; and
13 (b) Become licensed as a professional engineer or professional land surveyor in
14 the Commonwealth.
15 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 322 IS CREATED TO
16 READ AS FOLLOWS:
17 (1) There is hereby established in the State Treasury a trust and agency account to be
18 known as the Kentucky professional engineer and professional land surveyor
19 incentive scholarship fund. The fund shall consist of moneys received as
20 described in Section 4 of this Act.
21 (2) The fund shall be administered by the board.
22 (3) Amounts deposited in the fund shall be used for the scholarships established in
23 Section 3 of this Act.
24 (4) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of the
25 fiscal year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the next fiscal year.
26 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 322 IS CREATED TO
27 READ AS FOLLOWS:
Page 1 of 4
