UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1353
1 (1) The board shall make engineering and land surveying scholarships available to
2 Kentucky residents through the Kentucky professional engineer and professional
3 land surveyor incentive scholarship fund established in Section 2 of this Act in
4 accordance with Sections 1 to 4 of this Act and administrative regulations
5 promulgated pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A.
6 (2) The board shall administer the Kentucky professional engineer and professional
7 land surveyor incentive scholarship fund and may recover reasonable costs for
8 administering the fund. The board shall receive and evaluate all applications for
9 the scholarship made by bona fide Kentucky residents who desire to become
10 professional engineers or professional land surveyors. The board shall evaluate
11 each application to determine if the applicant complies with criteria for the
12 scholarships as set forth in this section and in the administrative regulations of
13 the board.
14 (3) From among the qualified applications, the board shall designate the persons to
15 receive assistance and the amount of the scholarship award. The board's
16 scholarship decisions shall be final. Disbursement of funds shall occur pursuant
17 to a written contract between the board and the applicant.
18 (4) The board shall annually determine the amount and number of individual
19 professional engineering and professional land surveying scholarship awards to
20 be granted by using its best judgment and shall seek to maintain the scholarship
21 funds for future use.
22 (5) Each recipient of a scholarship granted under Sections 1 to 4 of this Act shall
23 agree in the written contract to:
24 (a) Obtain a professional engineer or professional land surveyor license in
25 Kentucky within six (6) years of graduation; and
26 (b) Engage in the licensed practice of professional engineering or professional
27 land surveying in Kentucky for at least one (1) year for each academic year
Page 2 of 4
