UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1353
1 the recipient received the scholarship funds.
2 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 322 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 (1) Funding for the Kentucky professional engineer and professional land surveyor
5 incentive scholarship fund:
6 (a) Shall be supplied partly by funds received from penalties and fines assessed
7 by the board pursuant to KRS 322.180;
8 (b) Shall be provided by an assessment of five dollars ($5) from each
9 professional engineer and professional land surveyor licensure renewal
10 application fee payable to the board, the proceeds of which shall be
11 annually allocated to the Kentucky professional engineer and professional
12 land surveyor incentive scholarship fund; and
13 (c) May be provided by the board from its budgeted funds.
14 (2) (a) The board may cancel any contract entered into under Section 3 of this Act
15 if an applicant or recipient fails to meet the requirements of Section 3 of
16 this Act or the administrative regulations of the board.
17 (b) Failure to complete the terms of the contract shall subject the applicant to
18 legal action for the recovery of all assistance provided, along with the
19 attorney's fees and interest at an annual compound rate of eight percent
20 (8%) from the date of disbursement from the Kentucky professional
21 engineer and professional land surveyor incentive scholarship fund.
22 (3) By August 1 of each year, the board shall submit a report to the Legislative
23 Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Licensing,
24 Occupations, and Administrative Regulations relating to the Kentucky
25 professional engineer and professional land surveyor incentive scholarship fund.
26 The report shall contain at a minimum the following information for the previous
27 fiscal year:
Page 3 of 4
